Created by Spyro (CupoOci)

-----------------------------------------

A medium map for ZombieMod. There are a lot of secrets :)

25 slots per team.

This is a map geared more towards zombie mod (regular and horde) gameplay, if people seem to like it, I'll make a DE version. There are 50 terrorist spawns and 30 counter-terrorist spawns, terrorist spawn in the back and CT's spawn in the school and outside in the front. There are a few easter eggs, and the map is loosely based off of my school. There are three floors a basement, first floor, and second floor. 

The textures are included in the map, and it is 45 MB. (If anyone knows of a way to decrease the size, let me know without altering the actual map [except settings or adding something])

--SPOILER ALERT--


























SPOILER:
When you walk in, the lights turn off and can be turned on in the basement (the panel).

To start this off. I am not the original creator of this map. Nipper is the creator of cs_darkhouse. The only credit I take is for modifying it for zombiemod.

My clans zombiemod server originally had the cs_darkhouse version on their server over a year ago. It was played a good amount but really had no good places to hide or barricade. They layout of the map it's self is actually really good for zombiemod. It just needed a few tweeks. So a few weeks ago I decided to to take the map and zombify it. Changing things into moveable objects and a few spots into good camping spots. While most the map remains like the original. A few things have changed.

=========================

- The room is now accessable.
- Areas in attic to serve as camping spots.
- Moveable props all throughout the house now!
- Some doors have been closed for zombiemod.
- Some rooms have changed size a slight bit.
- There is now access to the top of the barn.
- Moveable props in the barn.
- Move able props in the shed.
- The rock with boxes stacked up to it is now larger.
- The underground has changed a slit bit for ZM and a small room was added.
- Terrorist spawns have been moved outside behind the house.

=========================

We have ran this map on the .Zpro server and people seemed to like it so I have decided to release it here. The original map had a great layout. It just needed to be zombified a bit. Though I would like to make it clear again that I am "NOT" the original creator of this map. I just took it and made a few changes here and there for zombiemod.

Enjoy.

This is the latest version of my port of the Duke Nukem 64 level, Hollywood Holocaust. The map name may seem confusing, but it's to differentiate from other PC ports with the same name. The Nintendo 64 version of Duke Nukem had different layouts for many of the levels, and I prefer the N64 layout over the PC layout.

If you've played either version of the game, you should easily be able to spot all of the secret areas, and as an added bonus, there is a jetpack in the level.

When you find the hidden jetpack, you must drop your pistol to pick it up. To use the jetpack, you must switch to your knife and press your alternate fire button to activate and deactivate it. Make sure that you're looking straight ahead while activating it, or you'll go careening around uncontrollably. The key to control is to activate the jetpack when looking straight forward. If you want to go backwards, look up slightly. If you want to go forwards, look down slightly. The farther you pitch up or down determines how fast you move in those directions. You can also strafe left and right fairly easily.

The jetpack has 120 seconds of fuel, less if you smash the activation key rapidly. I recommend using it in short bursts to maximize the amount of flight time you have.

I had originally planned on having a jetpack spawner in the level, but it proved to make the map far too hard for humans, and made the map unstable, as each jetpack used 15 entities each.
